<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-1803] Unwrap EntityManager to Connection</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-1803</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is currently the recommended way to access the javax.sql.Connection underlying an EntityManager:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        OpenJPAEntityManager oem = OpenJPAPersistence.cast(em);&lt;br/&gt;
        Connection con = (Connection) oem.getConnection();&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be more convenient to simply write&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        Connection con = em.unwrap(Connection.class);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That way, the client needing to access the Connection only depends on the javax.persistence API and not on org.apache.openjpa.*.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I believe the JPA 2.0 spec neither mandates nor forbids this functionality. It is supported by Eclipselink 2.x.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
